  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "Are there any plans for a `buidler node --fork` option as with Ganache, e.g. `ganache-cli --fork=${NODE_URL}` where `NODE_URL` can be, for example, an Infura mainnet node?\r\n\r\nRight now, due to lack of this feature, I don't see any way of doing integration testing with Buidler EVM, short of actually doing lengthy, complicated deploys of other people's contracts onto a local Buidler node.  I can of course just connect to Ganache, but then I'm not getting the cool Buidler EVM features like solidity stack traces, etc.",
